<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3854] &quot;Groovy executing&quot; dialog comes/stays forever although no script should be running</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3854</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When working with GroovyConsole, I quite often get a &quot;Groovy executing&quot; dialog although no script should be running. Mostly this happens when I switch back to the console after it has run in the background for some time. Usually, the only way to get rid of the dialog is to restart GroovyConsole. Another way to get a dialog that stays forever is to hit the run button as fast as you can for a few seconds. Easily reproducible for me.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Mac OS 10.6.1&lt;br/&gt;
Java 1.6.0_15</environment>
